I assume this is from using the incorrect labels file, when I use the pets label file in the blog post the index that triggers this error is smaller than in the error above.

However, I also updated tensorflow/models to master and ran export_tflite_ssd_graph.py on ssd_mobilenet_v2. This produced and error saying that batch_norm_trainable had been removed (which can be verified by looking at the logs). Therefore is ssd_mobilenet_v2 still supported? If it is, what was the most recent set of commits (for tensorflow/tensorflow and tensorflow/models) that it's been tested on? If not, A. is the model zoo going to be updated with this info and B. how do we determine which models are supported with which versions of TensorFlow?

body:
So the latest checkpoints are able to be loaded. Unfortunately they create the following error:
```
09-06 14:52:23.341  8812  8829 E AndroidRuntime: java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException: length=1280; index=-2147483647
09-06 14:52:23.341  8812  8829 E AndroidRuntime:        at java.util.Vector.elementData(Vector.java:734)
09-06 14:52:23.341  8812  8829 E AndroidRuntime:        at java.util.Vector.get(Vector.java:750)
09-06 14:52:23.341  8812  8829 E AndroidRuntime:        at org.tensorflow.demo.TFLiteObjectDetectionAPIModel.recognizeImage(TFLiteObjectDetectionAPIModel.java:214)
09-06 14:52:23.341  8812  8829 E AndroidRuntime:        at org.tensorflow.demo.DetectorActivity$3.run(DetectorActivity.java:247)
09-06 14:52:23.341  8812  8829 E AndroidRuntime:        at android.os.Handler.handleCallback(Handler.java:873)
09-06 14:52:23.341  8812  8829 E AndroidRuntime:        at android.os.Handler.dispatchMessage(Handler.java:99)
09-06 14:52:23.341  8812  8829 E AndroidRuntime:        at android.os.Looper.loop(Looper.java:193)
09-06 14:52:23.341  8812  8829 E AndroidRuntime:        at android.os.HandlerThread.run(HandlerThread.java:65)
09-06 14:52:23.345   914  1786 W ActivityManager:   Force finishing activity org.tensorflow.lite.demo/org.tensorflow.demo.DetectorActivity
```
I assume this is from using the incorrect labels file, when I use the pets label file in the blog post the index that triggers this error is smaller than in the error above.

However, I also updated tensorflow/models to master and ran export_tflite_ssd_graph.py on ssd_mobilenet_v2. This produced and error saying that `batch_norm_trainable` had been removed (which can be verified by looking at the logs). Therefore is ssd_mobilenet_v2 still supported? If it is, what was the most recent set of commits (for tensorflow/tensorflow and tensorflow/models) that it's been tested on? If not, A. is the model zoo going to be updated with this info and B. how do we determine which models are supported with which versions of TensorFlow?
